{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, the enhanced transparency achieved by simply making explicit what would otherwise remain implicit makes even this most straightforward approach an important step forward.",
    "The single theory approach consists of studying existing documentation about a specific theory.",
    "The primary source is often the work of the original author(s) of the theory.",
    "A benefit is that this approach requires limited resources.",
    "Moreover, this approach is probably easily applicable, because in theory, a theory should also specify how to develop a measurement instrument (and perhaps also how to conduct qualitative research using that theory)."
  ]
}